HANTAVIRUS UPDATE 2012 - AMERICAS (03): CHILE
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update:
[1] Chile (Nuble)
[2] Chile (Los Lagos)

******
[1] Chile (Nuble)
Date: Thu 26 Jan 2012
Source: La Discusion [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.diarioladiscusion.cl/index.php/noticias/100-salud1651607246/7660-isp-confirmo-caso-de-virus-hanta-en-estudiante-de-la-universidad-del-bio-bio


The Public Health Institute yesterday [26 Jan 2012] confirmed a case of [a] hantavirus [infection] in the Regional Hospital Guillermo Grant Benavente of Concepcion.

The report is of a young student of the Bio-Bio Chillan University, who resides in the Concepcion capital. The patient was admitted to hospital service with suspicious symptoms (fever, myalgia), because of which tests were carried out. Accpording to the Health SEREMI [regional governmental ministerial unit], the young person is currently in stable condition, progressing favorably in the intensive care unit of the Guillermo Grant Benavente Regional Hospital of Concepcion, information that was confirmed by the Nuble Health SEREMI, Paola Blasco.

The health authorities still are not clear about where the infection was acquired, although it is suspected that the youth might have contracted the disease [infection] in the Pinto community of the Los Lleuques locale.

As for the date of the infection, it is estimated that it was between 24 - 28 Dec [2011], so the case was included in the 2011 statistics. Given this, there were 14 cases that occurred in the region last year [2011]. The prevalence rate is 0.68 cases per 100 000 population, and the fatality rate is 42.8 per cent.

When and if the locality of infection of the university youth is confirmed as Los Lleuques, the number of cases registered in Nuble during 2011 would increase to 4.

--
